# Wire-format TYPE snapshot — DO NOT edit by hand.
# File: snapshots/wire_values.snap
# Each entry is the postcard byte encoding of one wire-type exemplar. A diff
# here means a type's payload encoding changed (field reorder, variant
# renumber, …). If intentional, bump ProtocolVersion::CURRENT and regenerate:
#   UPDATE_SNAPSHOTS=1 cargo test -p rmk-types --features rynk wire_values
# Format: <label>  <hex bytes>

